	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Ok, someone asked why the combine is better than the mino axe, well friends welcome to weapons 101.  let's examine both weapons, we'll start with attack delay, the mino is 37 while the combine is 28, combine is a good amount faster. Now let's look at damage, the mino is 8 while the combine is 6 now you may be saying &quot;HAH, the Mino does more damage&quot; Now while that may be true with the speed of the combine you should actually be killing the badies quicker. Next we look at the weight of the items (granted not the most important factor but non the less one to be addressed) the Mino weighs in at 8.5 and the combine weighs in at 5, so if you are duel wielding your total weapon weight with Mino's is 17 and with combines is 10 a 7 difference.  Lastly let's look at one last item here, the Mino is Non (I repeat) Non magical while the combine is (I repeat) IS magical.  Won't be doing to much Wisp killing with Mino's now will ya :-)  So in conclusion the combine is faster only does 2 less damage weighs a lot less and is Magical.  Hmmm I think I will use Combines when giving the oppurtunity  Class Dismissed
			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
